Fast JSON Parser for .NET

39% less time than Newtonsoft.Json using 31% less memory. (As measured on M2 MacBook Pro Max.)

Uses ReadOnlyMemory<char> instead of string for speed and memory efficiency.

No dependencies. No support for JSONPath, JSON Schema or LINQ to JSON. No support for deserialization to .NET objects
or serialization from them. Does not parse JSON literals to value types, such as booleans, null or numbers. Since JSON
numbers are not bounded by rules of IEEE 754 floating point, they can be arbitrarily large or precise.